# Event Host тАУ Remaining Features Implementation Plan

The project already has the `events` table with `status`, `approved_by`, `approved_at`, `rejected_at`, and `reject_reason` columns тАФ so the approval DB schema is already done. The [show.tsx](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/resources/js/pages/feats/events/show.tsx) page has a placeholder "Join Event" button and hardcoded spot counts. These three features wire everything up properly.

---

## Feature A тАУ User Event Registration (Join / Leave)

### Backend

#### [NEW] `create_event_registrations_table` migration
- Columns: `id`, `event_id` (FK тЖТ events), `user_id` (FK тЖТ users), `status` (enum: registered/cancelled), `joined_at`, `timestamps`
- Unique constraint: [(event_id, user_id)](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/database/migrations/2026_02_19_094228_create_events_table.php#9-32) тАФ one registration per user per event

#### [NEW] `EventRegistration.php` model
- `belongsTo(Event)`, `belongsTo(User)`
- `$fillable`: `event_id`, `user_id`, `status`, `joined_at`

#### [MODIFY] [Event.php](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Models/Event.php)
- Add `hasMany(EventRegistration::class)` relationship
- Add `registrations_count` via `withCount` (not a local attribute тАФ loaded by controller)

#### [NEW] `EventRegistrationController.php`
- [store(Event $event)](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/EventController.php#40-73) тАУ join: validate not full, not already registered, event is approved; create record
- [destroy(Event $event)](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/EventController.php#128-137) тАУ leave: find and delete/cancel the registration
- [index()](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/AdminDashboardController.php#14-21) тАУ list events the authenticated user has joined тЖТ renders `feats/user/my-registrations`

#### [MODIFY] [EventController.php](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/EventController.php) ([show](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/EventController.php#74-83))
- Eager-load `registrations_count` and check if `auth()->user()` has a registration (`userRegistered`)
- Pass both values to Inertia

#### [MODIFY] [web.php](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/routes/web.php)
- Under `user.` middleware group:
  - `POST /user/events/{event}/join` тЖТ `EventRegistrationController@store`
  - `DELETE /user/events/{event}/leave` тЖТ `EventRegistrationController@destroy`
  - `GET /user/my-registrations` тЖТ `EventRegistrationController@index`

### Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [show.tsx](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/resources/js/pages/feats/events/show.tsx)
- Replace hardcoded spots with `event.capacity` and `event.registrations_count`
- Real progress bar fill: [(registrations_count / capacity) * 100](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/database/migrations/2026_02_19_094228_create_events_table.php#9-32)%
- "Join Event" / "Leave Event" toggle based on `userRegistered` prop
- Disable button + show "Full" badge when `registrations_count >= capacity`
- Sonner toast on success/error

#### [NEW] `feats/user/my-registrations.tsx`
- Table/card list of events the user has joined
- Show event title, date, location, status badge

