## Feature B тАУ Admin Event Approval

> [!NOTE]
> The `events` table already has all needed columns (`status`, `approved_by`, `approved_at`, `rejected_at`, `reject_reason`). No new migration needed.

### Backend

#### [NEW] `AdminEventController.php`
- [index()](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/AdminDashboardController.php#14-21) тАУ list all events with host info, filter by status query param
- `approve(Event $event)` тАУ set `status=approved`, `approved_by`, `approved_at`
- `reject(Request $request, Event $event)` тАУ validate `reject_reason`, set `status=rejected`, `rejected_at`, `reject_reason`

#### [MODIFY] [EventController.php](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/EventController.php)
- [index()](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/AdminDashboardController.php#14-21): only show `approved` events (public listing)
- [show()](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/EventController.php#74-83): return 404 if event is not `approved`. Exception: allow host to see own pending/rejected events
- [store()](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/app/Http/Controllers/EventController.php#40-73): after creating, redirect with a "pending approval" flash message

#### [MODIFY] [web.php](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/routes/web.php)
- Under `admin.` middleware group:
  - `GET /admin/events` тЖТ `AdminEventController@index`
  - `POST /admin/events/{event}/approve` тЖТ `AdminEventController@approve`
  - `POST /admin/events/{event}/reject` тЖТ `AdminEventController@reject`

### Frontend

#### [NEW] `feats/admin/events.tsx`
- Table with columns: Title, Host name, Status badge, Created At, Actions
- Filter tabs: All / Pending / Approved / Rejected
- **Approve** button тЖТ Inertia POST to approve route
- **Reject** button тЖТ opens Dialog with textarea for reject reason тЖТ Inertia POST

#### [MODIFY] [admin-layout.tsx](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/resources/js/pages/feats/admin/admin-layout.tsx)
- Add "Events" link in the sidebar nav

#### [MODIFY] [show.tsx](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/resources/js/pages/feats/events/show.tsx)
- If event `status === 'pending'`, show a yellow info banner: "This event is awaiting admin approval and is not yet publicly visible."
- If event `status === 'rejected'`, show a red banner with `reject_reason`

#### [MODIFY] [my-events.tsx](file:///Users/apwiz/msc/web/project/event-host/resources/js/pages/feats/events/my-events.tsx) (host)
- Show status badge (Pending / Approved / Rejected) next to each event
- If rejected, show the reject reason in a collapsible tooltip or inline text

